<div class="os-eoc os-exercises-container" data-type="composite-page" data-uuid-key=".exercises"><section class="exercises" data-depth="1" id="fs-idp13430448"><h3 data-type="document-title" id="[redacted for uniqueness]"><span class="os-number">3.1</span><span class="os-divider"> </span><span class="os-text">Formula Mass and the Mole Concept</span></h3>
<div class=" os-hasSolution " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp14760336">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm9492960"><a class="os-number" href="chapter-3#fs-idp14760336-solution">1</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idp66967088">What is the total mass (amu) of carbon in each of the following molecules?</p>
<p id="fs-idp15394896">(a) CH<sub>4</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp74952320">(b) CHCl<sub>3</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp16776928">(c) C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>10</sub>O<sub>6</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm16945392">(d) CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>3</sub></p>
</div></div>

</div>
<div class=" " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp23290000">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm3204960"><span class="os-number">2</span><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idp12657920">What is the total mass of hydrogen in each of the molecules?</p>
<p id="fs-idp14913040">(a) CH<sub>4</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp13933872">(b) CHCl<sub>3</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp18791104">(c) C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>10</sub>O<sub>6</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm2014656">(d) CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CH<sub>3</sub></p>
</div></div>
</div>
<div class=" os-hasSolution " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp14091664">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idp13719856"><a class="os-number" href="chapter-3#fs-idp14091664-solution">3</a><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
<p id="fs-idm4748784">Calculate the molecular or formula mass of each of the following:</p>
<p id="fs-idp75123488">(a) P<sub>4</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idp11323648">(b) H<sub>2</sub>O</p>
<p id="fs-idp17374816">(c) Ca(NO<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub></p>
<p id="fs-idm4666224">(d) CH<sub>3</sub>CO<sub>2</sub>H (acetic acid)</p>
<p id="fs-idp17618896">(e) C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>22</sub>O<sub>11</sub> (sucrose, cane sugar)</p></div></div>

</div>
